Beneficiaries reached is 0, as the construction and rehabilitation of toilet blocks is not completed and not handed over (yet) to Schools students and staff. Construction work for 40 toilets in ongoing and reached to 40% of its completion. Rehabilitation of 20 old pit latrines (K. Kunar, Surkhrod, Goshta) is also ongoing, which includes changing pit latrines to flush toilets. Construction of 6 handwashing stations is completed, but not (yet) connected to water pipe network for supply of water to the HW stations.

First round of hygiene promotion took place in all schools, and soaps will be distributed during the third round, expected towards the end of the year (schools are currently on summer vacation until Sept). Soap will be distributed in Q4

Beneficiaries covered is 9.675 in Q3 by drilling of 6 bore wells (2 in Kuz Kunar, 3 in Surkhrud, 1 in Goshta), completed in all 6 schools. Boreholes supported by both handpumps and submersible. Handpumps in use by students and staff. Submersible not yet in use for provision of drinking water, as not yet connected with water tanks and taps. Connection work with tanks and taps planned for Q4.

In Q2 IRC successfully conducted the 1st round of hygiene promotion in the 7 targeted schools. During the session, beneficiaries learned about critical times for handwashing, personal and environmental hygiene and safe water sources and usage. In Q3, September, 356 girls received 1st session of hygiene promotion training in 1 Girls school, Surkhrod

In 2019, IRC provided temporary and 
emergency shelter to improve living conditions for conflict and natural disaster affected IDPs living in the open or makeshift shelters in Behsud, Kuz Kunar and Surkhrud districts of Nangahar province. The IRC provided 80 households (508 individuals - 171 girls, 160 boys, 96 women , 81 men) with temporary shelters which ensured dignity, improved quality of life, and provided an immediate solution to those families living under the open sky. Moreover, the IRC distributed to 275 households (1,655
 individuals – 518 girls, 566 boys, 305 women and 266 men) cluster standard emergency shelter as immediate shelter response.
